com.guidewire.ab.webservices.entity

Class TempToPermEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.guidewire.ab.webservices.entity.GWObject
      • com.guidewire.ab.webservices.entity.TempToPermEntry
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class TempToPermEntry
extends GWObject
implements java.io.Serializable
    After an addressbook client-application (for example, ClaimCenter) adds an entity (for example, Contact or Address) to the addressbook, it usually needs to link the local entity to the newly created entity in the addressbook by setting the AddressBookUId in the local entity. After calling AddressBookPluginGateway.submitUpdates(UpdateBatch,AddressBookConvertable) the client application can get the newly generated AddressBookUId from the ContactUpdateResult.getTempToPermEntrys().
